title: For Sale:  German Occupation FN High Power 9mm  RARE
postcontent:
Up for sale German Occupation FN High Power 9mm.  Verified through FN.  Gun and Holster has Reich markings.  Will post better pictures soon.


  Story behind the handgun is:

In the spring of 1945, the 3rd Infantry Division was approaching the end of their involvement in WW2. My father was  ranger in the division's 7th regiment and he was sent to blow up a RR tunnel that connected to Berchtesgaden which was Hitler's summer home. After they blew the tunnel they took the train and there was a German civilian engineer and coalman on it. They said that the train was otherwise empty but that the caboose was Herman Gerrig's personal car. He was the commander of the German Air Force. In the desk drawer was this F-N 9mm Luger.

 Best Offers Will Be Considered.  No trades or low-ball offers.  Will post better pictures soon.  If close ups of any area are wanted, please ask.
